<h2 id="fulfillment-delivery">📦 Fulfillment and Delivery: The Final Impression</h2>

<h3>White-Glove Fulfillment Requirements</h3>

Luxury fulfillment extends far beyond getting packages to doorsteps. Your fulfillment operation must support signature packaging, personalized enclosures, scheduled delivery windows, and the handling standards that protect high-value merchandise.

For brands with substantial e-commerce volume, ShipBob's premium fulfillment tier offers temperature control, custom packaging insertion, and the accuracy rates necessary when each shipment represents a significant transaction. The integration with Shopify Plus provides real-time inventory sync and automated routing.

Smaller luxury operators often benefit from hybrid approaches—handling VIP and high-value orders in-house while using 3PL partners for standard shipments. Your technology must support this routing logic based on order characteristics.

<h3>Last-Mile Excellence</h3>

Standard carrier delivery rarely meets luxury expectations. White-glove delivery services like Deliv, Roadie, or local courier partnerships enable scheduled delivery windows, in-person handoffs, and the presentation standards that complete the luxury experience.

Your tech stack must integrate these options at checkout, presenting appropriate delivery choices based on order value, customer tier, and location. A $200 purchase might ship standard; a $5,000 purchase justifies premium delivery investment.

